All of her highlights in the show so far was through surprise factor, assists, team combos and straight out flukes. She wouldn't catch 13 a second time like that, nor Toga (provided that Toga isn't messing around by gushing about the psycho-crush she has on her). I could easily see this being a thing in the hero academy world. Underground trafficking with captured heroes or civilians or heck, even villians. In a world with rampant meta power wielding mutants, this is certainly a possibility, and the U.A students are, specially class 1-A apparently, famous, so some fuck loaded with money, power and influence with connections could have something like this arranged. Honestly, she should've known better then going solo like that, her power is more suited for being a rescue type hero, removing debris or making supplies/items/tools/victims/heroes lighter to facilitate/ensure rescue operations, at best, she could be an ambush type assist combat support in a team. Her "Gunhead Martial Arts" is practically a meme, not a show stopper. Being famous through the sports festival means that, for better or worse (worse), all villians who keep up with trends and news such as upcoming and ongoing active heroes will know her power and what she's about.
